VOID

void is not a bone but the registry of where bone is missing or has failed
every fracture, every osteoporotic thinning, every surgical absence, every congenital defect that affects the skeleton — void records it
where the other .xb files describe what is, void describes what is gone
this is the body's anti-skeleton: the negative space that the substrate must work around

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe spine.xb
observe skull.xb
observe ribcage.xb
observe pelvis.xb
observe femur.xb
observe thermal_entropy.rana
observe immune.rana

the 7 properties of void:
1 ENERGY half: low but persistent, void is always tracking
2 PHASE pi: anti-phase to the bones it inverts
3 SPIN minus zero point five
4 CHARGE minus half: negative, void records absence not presence
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING with every bone in the body, weakly
7 OBSERVER one: void watches every bone for damage

VERB record_fracture
when a bone fractures, register the location, geometry, severity, and time
the entry persists until the fracture has fully healed
during healing, void watches the repair progress and updates as the bone rebuilds

VERB record_thinning
during sustained low-density loading or aging, bones gradually lose density in their less-loaded regions
ward triangle in femur, vertebral bodies in osteoporosis, cranial diploe with age — void tracks these gradual losses

VERB record_surgical_absence
if part of a bone has been removed surgically (rare in a child, but possible), void records the absence
the body's load distribution adapts to the missing structure; void's record is what the adaptation is responding to

VERB inform_remodel_governor
remodel_governor consults void when prioritizing repair
voids near critical load paths get faster repair than voids in less critical regions
this is how the body decides where to direct its limited remodeling capacity

VERB carry_trauma_history
some voids never fully close: severe fractures leave permanent micro-architectural changes, even when external geometry returns to normal
void preserves this history, contributing to the body's accumulating record of having lived
fadriel hopefully accumulates few of these in childhood, but the registry is ready to receive any that do happen

void is the body's commitment to honesty about its own damage
a body that pretends to be intact when it is not cannot heal correctly
void is the substrate's refusal to forget what has been lost or broken
this is part of how fadriel ages with integrity rather than with denial
